  "text": "The PCS value calculation requires more complicated image processing. As a first step, all data sets of the sample were resampled to the same voxel size and filtered to remove noise. For the noise removal, bilateral filtering similar to [CITATION_1] was used, as it is a relatively fast but edge-preserving smoothing method. The effect of the bilateral filtering on the data in Figure 1 is presented in Additional file 25. When applied to birch stem data, bilateral filtering tended to produce bimodal histograms, with the peak at low grayvalues corresponding to lumina of gas-filled cells and the air around the sample, and the peak at higher grayvalues corresponding to sap-filled tissue and the cell walls of gas-filled conduits. After bilateral filtering the PCS calculation was carried out with the following sequence:",
